Class FeatureContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mapbox.services.geocoding.v5.models.FeatureContext

  • public class FeatureContext
extends java.lang.Object
    Feature context breaks down the places address and gives you more information about each part. In the case of an address it can give you the type id for each part and its name.

      • getId

        public java.lang.String getId()
        Feature IDs are formatted like {type}.{id}. {type} is one of the following, "country", "region", "postcode", "place", "locality", "neighborhood", "address", or poi. Additional feature types may be added in the future, but the current types will stay the same. The numeric part of a feature ID may change between data updates.
        Returns:
        String with format {type}.{id}.
